article.description: Armel Potter scored a career-high 27 points with eight rebounds and Charleston Southern defeated Presbyterian 77-63 on Thursday night, notching a 10th-straight win over Presbyterian in five seaso
article.headline: Potter's 27 aids Charleston Southern past Presbyterian 77-63
article.linkText: Potter's 27 aids Charleston Southern past Presbyterian 77-63
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Armel Potter scored a career-high 27 points with eight rebounds and Charleston Southern defeated Presbyterian 77-63 on Thursday night, notching a 10th-straight win over Presbyterian in five seasons. The duo of Patrick Wallace and Reuben King scored 13 points each and Javis Howard added 12 for Charleston Southern (9-16, 5-9 Big South).er scored a career-high 27 points with eight rebounds and Charleston Southern defeated Presbyterian 77-63 on Thursday night, notching a 10-straight win over Presbyterian in five seasons. Presbyterian (8-16, 3-10) got off to a cold start, making 6 of 21 field goals in the first half, and trailed 37-23 at the break. DeSean Murray led the Blue Hose with 18 points -- 15 in the first half -- and Reggie Dillard added 12. Presbyterian came as close as nine points early in the second half on a Murray free throw. Charleston Southern outrebounded Presbyterian 43-27 with 14 offensive boards that led to 16 second-chance points.
